Holdout execution is blocked because the experiment/scenario runner has no scenario-root or
scenario-directory input and resolves manifests, fixtures, and hidden checks from a compile-time
monorepo root. The smallest required seam is a path-contained `--scenario-root evals/holdout` input
that reuses existing executor IDs and records the selected scenario version and computed fixture
hash in the report. The private suite, safe mount, documentation, hashes, commits, and three required
green gates are delivered; runner/evaluator code remains untouched per the hard write scope.
